{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_0135Vv2PAd2kcwe3Vg8Eojr7","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Reliability: Multiarch Tuning Operator\n2\t\n3\t## SLO Targets\n4\t\n5\t| SLO | Target | Measured by |\n6\t|---|---|---|\n7\t| Gate-to-schedule latency P50 | < 2 seconds | `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds` |\n8\t| Gate-to-schedule latency P99 | < 10 seconds | `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds` |\n9\t| Webhook availability | 99.9% | `kube_deployment_status_replicas_available` for webhook deployment |\n10\t| Image inspection success rate | > 95% | `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` vs `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` |\n11\t\n12\t## Metric Naming Convention\n13\t\n14\tMetrics follow a two-level prefix scheme:\n15\t\n16\t- **Controller metrics**: `mto_ppo_ctrl_*` — emitted by the pod placement controller (`--enable-ppc-controllers`)\n17\t- **Webhook metrics**: `mto_ppo_wh_*` — emitted by the mutating webhook (`--enable-ppc-webhook`)\n18\t- **Shared metrics**: `mto_ppo_*` (no subsystem) — emitted by both, initialized once via `onceCommon`\n19\t\n20\tAll metrics are registered using `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/metrics`'s `Registry.MustRegister(...)`.\n21\t\n22\t## Metric Catalog\n23\t\n24\t### Controller Metrics (`internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go`)\n25\t\n26\t| Metric | Type | Description |\n27\t|---|---|---|\n28\t| `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_pod_seconds` | Histogram | Time to process any pod (gated or not) |\n29\t| `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds` | Histogram | Time to process a gated pod, including image inspection; this is the gate-to-schedule latency |\n30\t| `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds` | Histogram | Time to inspect a single container image (per-image, not per-pod) |\n31\t| `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_pod_images_seconds` | Histogram | Time to inspect all container images in a pod |\n32\t| `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` | Counter | Total gated pods successfully processed by the controller |\n33\t| `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` | Counter | Total image inspection attempts that failed (each retry counts) |\n34\t\n35\t### Webhook Metrics (`internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/webhook.go`)\n36\t\n37\t| Metric | Type | Description |\n38\t|---|---|---|\n39\t| `mto_ppo_wh_pods_processed_total` | Counter | Total pods evaluated by the webhook (gated + ignored) |\n40\t| `mto_ppo_wh_pods_gated_total` | Counter | Total pods that received the scheduling gate |\n41\t| `mto_ppo_wh_response_time_seconds` | Histogram | Webhook handler response time (admission latency) |\n42\t\n43\t### Shared Metrics (`internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/common_metrics.go`)\n44\t\n45\t| Metric | Type | Description |\n46\t|---|---|---|\n47\t| `mto_ppo_pods_gated` | Gauge | Current number of pods holding the scheduling gate; labeled as \"not reliable yet\" pending full reconciliation coverage |\n48\t\n49\t## PromQL Examples\n50\t\n51\t### Image Inspection Failure Rate (SLI)\n52\t\n53\tThe image inspection failure rate is the primary reliability SLI. It measures what fraction of processed pods encountered at least one image inspection failure:\n54\t\n55\t```promql\n56\t# Failure rate over 5-minute windows\n57\trate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[5m])\n58\t/\n59\trate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[5m])\n60\t```\n61\t\n62\tThis gives a ratio between 0 and (potentially > 1 if a pod fails inspection multiple times). Normalize for alerting:\n63\t\n64\t```promql\n65\t# Alert-friendly: failure rate > 5% triggers critical\n66\t(\n67\t  rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[10m])\n68\t  /\n69\t  rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[10m])\n70\t) > 0.05\n71\t```\n72\t\n73\t### Gate-to-Schedule Latency Percentiles\n74\t\n75\t```promql\n76\t# P50 latency\n77\thistogram_quantile(0.50, rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds_bucket[5m]))\n78\t\n79\t# P99 latency\n80\thistogram_quantile(0.99, rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds_bucket[5m]))\n81\t\n82\t# Alert: P99 > 10s\n83\thistogram_quantile(0.99, rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds_bucket[5m])) > 10\n84\t```\n85\t\n86\t### Webhook Admission Latency\n87\t\n88\t```promql\n89\t# P99 webhook response time\n90\thistogram_quantile(0.99, rate(mto_ppo_wh_response_time_seconds_bucket[5m]))\n91\t\n92\t# Gate rate (pods gated per second)\n93\trate(mto_ppo_wh_pods_gated_total[5m])\n94\t\n95\t# Fraction of evaluated pods that get gated (sanity check — should be close to 1.0 for non-excluded namespaces)\n96\trate(mto_ppo_wh_pods_gated_total[5m]) / rate(mto_ppo_wh_pods_processed_total[5m])\n97\t```\n98\t\n99\t### Per-Image vs Per-Pod Inspection Time\n100\t\n101\t```promql\n102\t# Average time to inspect a single image\n103\trate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds_sum[5m])\n104\t/\n105\trate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds_count[5m])\n106\t\n107\t# Average total time to inspect all images in a pod\n108\trate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_pod_images_seconds_sum[5m])\n109\t/\n110\trate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_pod_images_seconds_count[5m])\n111\t```\n112\t\n113\t## Alerting Thresholds\n114\t\n115\t| Alert | Condition | Severity | Notes |\n116\t|---|---|---|---|\n117\t| ImageInspectionFailureRateHigh | `rate(failed)[10m] / rate(processed)[10m] > 0.05` | Critical | Image inspection failure rate exceeds 5%; pods will be stuck gated or use fallback architecture |\n118\t| GateToScheduleLatencyHigh | `histogram_quantile(0.99, ...) > 10` | Warning | P99 gate-to-schedule time exceeds SLO |\n119\t| WebhookLatencyHigh | `histogram_quantile(0.99, mto_ppo_wh_response_time_seconds_bucket ...) > 1` | Warning | Webhook admission taking > 1s P99 |\n120\t\n121\tThe image inspection failure rate threshold of 5% (0.05) is the critical boundary: above this rate, a significant fraction of pods will be stuck waiting for scheduling or relying on `fallbackArchitecture`. If `fallbackArchitecture` is not set, they will be stuck gated indefinitely after `MaxRetryCount` (5) exhaustion.\n122\t\n123\t## Metrics Initialization\n124\t\n125\tMetrics are initialized lazily via `sync.Once` guards to allow the same binary to potentially run different subsets:\n126\t\n127\t- `InitPodPlacementControllerMetrics()` — called during `--enable-ppc-controllers` setup\n128\t- `InitWebhookMetrics()` — called during `--enable-ppc-webhook` setup\n129\t- `initCommonMetrics()` — called internally by both, guarded by `onceCommon`\n130\t\n131\tSee `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/` for full implementation. The ServiceMonitor for Prometheus scraping is created by the operator controller (`--enable-operator` mode) when it manages the CPPC lifecycle.\n132\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"79495011-2715-4b94-916d-03b0bb89c758","uuid":"d6b5205c-f226-4a06-874f-c92775313763","timestamp":"2026-07-20T18:30:29.977Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment/agentic/RELIABILITY.md","content":"# Reliability: Multiarch Tuning Operator\n\n## SLO Targets\n\n| SLO | Target | Measured by |\n|---|---|---|\n| Gate-to-schedule latency P50 | < 2 seconds | `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds` |\n| Gate-to-schedule latency P99 | < 10 seconds | `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds` |\n| Webhook availability | 99.9% | `kube_deployment_status_replicas_available` for webhook deployment |\n| Image inspection success rate | > 95% | `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` vs `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` |\n\n## Metric Naming Convention\n\nMetrics follow a two-level prefix scheme:\n\n- **Controller metrics**: `mto_ppo_ctrl_*` — emitted by the pod placement controller (`--enable-ppc-controllers`)\n- **Webhook metrics**: `mto_ppo_wh_*` — emitted by the mutating webhook (`--enable-ppc-webhook`)\n- **Shared metrics**: `mto_ppo_*` (no subsystem) — emitted by both, initialized once via `onceCommon`\n\nAll metrics are registered using `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/metrics`'s `Registry.MustRegister(...)`.\n\n## Metric Catalog\n\n### Controller Metrics (`internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go`)\n\n| Metric | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_pod_seconds` | Histogram | Time to process any pod (gated or not) |\n| `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds` | Histogram | Time to process a gated pod, including image inspection; this is the gate-to-schedule latency |\n| `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds` | Histogram | Time to inspect a single container image (per-image, not per-pod) |\n| `mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_pod_images_seconds` | Histogram | Time to inspect all container images in a pod |\n| `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` | Counter | Total gated pods successfully processed by the controller |\n| `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` | Counter | Total image inspection attempts that failed (each retry counts) |\n\n### Webhook Metrics (`internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/webhook.go`)\n\n| Metric | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `mto_ppo_wh_pods_processed_total` | Counter | Total pods evaluated by the webhook (gated + ignored) |\n| `mto_ppo_wh_pods_gated_total` | Counter | Total pods that received the scheduling gate |\n| `mto_ppo_wh_response_time_seconds` | Histogram | Webhook handler response time (admission latency) |\n\n### Shared Metrics (`internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/common_metrics.go`)\n\n| Metric | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `mto_ppo_pods_gated` | Gauge | Current number of pods holding the scheduling gate; labeled as \"not reliable yet\" pending full reconciliation coverage |\n\n## PromQL Examples\n\n### Image Inspection Failure Rate (SLI)\n\nThe image inspection failure rate is the primary reliability SLI. It measures what fraction of processed pods encountered at least one image inspection failure:\n\n```promql\n# Failure rate over 5-minute windows\nrate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[5m])\n/\nrate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[5m])\n```\n\nThis gives a ratio between 0 and (potentially > 1 if a pod fails inspection multiple times). Normalize for alerting:\n\n```promql\n# Alert-friendly: failure rate > 5% triggers critical\n(\n  rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[10m])\n  /\n  rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[10m])\n) > 0.05\n```\n\n### Gate-to-Schedule Latency Percentiles\n\n```promql\n# P50 latency\nhistogram_quantile(0.50, rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds_bucket[5m]))\n\n# P99 latency\nhistogram_quantile(0.99, rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds_bucket[5m]))\n\n# Alert: P99 > 10s\nhistogram_quantile(0.99, rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_process_gated_pod_seconds_bucket[5m])) > 10\n```\n\n### Webhook Admission Latency\n\n```promql\n# P99 webhook response time\nhistogram_quantile(0.99, rate(mto_ppo_wh_response_time_seconds_bucket[5m]))\n\n# Gate rate (pods gated per second)\nrate(mto_ppo_wh_pods_gated_total[5m])\n\n# Fraction of evaluated pods that get gated (sanity check — should be close to 1.0 for non-excluded namespaces)\nrate(mto_ppo_wh_pods_gated_total[5m]) / rate(mto_ppo_wh_pods_processed_total[5m])\n```\n\n### Per-Image vs Per-Pod Inspection Time\n\n```promql\n# Average time to inspect a single image\nrate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds_sum[5m])\n/\nrate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_image_seconds_count[5m])\n\n# Average total time to inspect all images in a pod\nrate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_pod_images_seconds_sum[5m])\n/\nrate(mto_ppo_ctrl_time_to_inspect_pod_images_seconds_count[5m])\n```\n\n## Alerting Thresholds\n\n| Alert | Condition | Severity | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| ImageInspectionFailureRateHigh | `rate(failed)[10m] / rate(processed)[10m] > 0.05` | Critical | Image inspection failure rate exceeds 5%; pods will be stuck gated or use fallback architecture |\n| GateToScheduleLatencyHigh | `histogram_quantile(0.99, ...) > 10` | Warning | P99 gate-to-schedule time exceeds SLO |\n| WebhookLatencyHigh | `histogram_quantile(0.99, mto_ppo_wh_response_time_seconds_bucket ...) > 1` | Warning | Webhook admission taking > 1s P99 |\n\nThe image inspection failure rate threshold of 5% (0.05) is the critical boundary: above this rate, a significant fraction of pods will be stuck waiting for scheduling or relying on `fallbackArchitecture`. If `fallbackArchitecture` is not set, they will be stuck gated indefinitely after `MaxRetryCount` (5) exhaustion.\n\n## Metrics Initialization\n\nMetrics are initialized lazily via `sync.Once` guards to allow the same binary to potentially run different subsets:\n\n- `InitPodPlacementControllerMetrics()` — called during `--enable-ppc-controllers` setup\n- `InitWebhookMetrics()` — called during `--enable-ppc-webhook` setup\n- `initCommonMetrics()` — called internally by both, guarded by `onceCommon`\n\nSee `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/` for full implementation. The ServiceMonitor for Prometheus scraping is created by the operator controller (`--enable-operator` mode) when it manages the CPPC lifecycle.\n","numLines":132,"startLine":1,"totalLines":132}}}
