as specified.\n- **Metrics used**: `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` and `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` — the two counters defined in `internal/controller/podplacement/metrics/controller.go:58-69`.\n- **Expression**: `rate(failed[10m]) / rate(processed[10m]) > 0.05` — taken directly from the alerting thresholds in `agentic/RELIABILITY.md:117` which specifies a 10-minute window and 5% (0.05) threshold for the `ImageInspectionFailureRateHigh` critical alert.\n- **`for: 5m`**: Prevents transient spikes from firing the alert; the condition must persist for 5 minutes.\n- **`namespace: system`**: Uses the `system` placeholder consistent with other config resources (`monitor.yaml`, `monitoring_role.yaml`); kustomize's `namespace` transformer in `config/default/kustomization.yaml` rewrites this to `openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator`.\n- **Placement**: `config/monitoring/` rather than `config/prometheus/` to separate the PrometheusRule (alerting) from the ServiceMonitor (scraping).\n\n## Commands to run\n\n```bash\n# No code generation needed — this is pure YAML.\n# Verify kustomize builds cleanly:\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment\nmake manifests   # regenerates CRD/RBAC, also validates kustomize overlay\n```\n\nIf `make manifests` doesn't exercise the default kustomization, you can verify independently:\n\n```bash\nkustomize build config/default\n```\n\nThis should include the PrometheusRule in the output with the correct namespace (`openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator`) and name prefix (`multiarch-tuning-operator-image-inspection-alerts`)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":567,"cache_read_input_tokens":41737,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":567,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"79495011-2715-4b94-916d-03b0bb89c758","uuid":"3b4